# Nmap Recon Report

## Objective - To perform reconnaissance on a target system using Nmap and identify open ports and services.

## Target (scanme.nmap.org)

## Scan Commands Used
nmap -sV scanme.nmap.org
nmap -A scanme.nmap.org

## Scan Results

## Open Ports & Services
22 -> SSH (profile login) *brute force
80 -> HTTP (website not-secure) *vulnerable
9929 -> Uncommon/Unknown Port
31337 -> Uncommon/Unknown port

## Analysis
### Port 22 (SSH)
This allows profile login. Attackers are capable of getting in through brute force


### Port 80 (HTTP)
This is an unsecure website. There are many vulnerablilities due to there being no encryption.
Vulnerablilities: 
-SQL Injection
-XSS


### Port 9929
This is a non=standard port with no recognizable default service
Vulnerablilities:
-could run an unknown applicaiton
-unknown services can increase attack surface
### Port 31337
This is a non-standard port often associated with a backdoor or test service. Its presence may indicate a hidden or non=public service
Vulnerabilities:
-Could be used for unauthorized access
-May run custom or vulnerable software

