### Non-Standard Ports
9929 and 31337 are non-standard ports that may lead to custom or test services
These ports are important because:
-They could run unpacthed or unknown software
-They increase attack service
-Attackers will check these for further investigation

## Connection to Email Security
- SMTP runs on port 25
- Attackers can scan for open mail servers
- Open email servers can be used for phishing/spoofing

